                  "id": "1eMhM",
                  "fill": "#22d3ee",
                  "content": "ANIMATION BEHAVIOR",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 10,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": 3
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "Wts3p",
                  "fill": "#94a3b8",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Entry: IntersectionObserver triggers serpentine CRT raster scan — Row 1 L→R, Row 2 R→L, Row 3 L→R. Each dot flares white-bright then settles to accent color. Number counts up in sync.\n\nHover: Nearest dot to cursor flares with pulse ring (::after scale 1→2.5, opacity→0). Label shows hex address: ADDR: 0x{row}:{col}. Moving slowly across grid feels like running finger across a control panel.\n\nDot meaning: Each dot = one real data point. Card 1: ~24 provider dots (sized by model count). Card 2: benchmark grid. Card 3: exactly 25 status provider nodes in a 5x5 grid.\n\nReduced-motion: all dots visible at final opacity, no scan, hover still works.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.6,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
